## Design Principles Derived from Research

### Core Principles for ADHD/Neurodivergent Users

#### 1. Remove decisions, don't organize them
- System decides, user approves
- No browsing recipe libraries
- Automation over configuration

#### 2. Reduce cognitive load
- Single-column layouts
- Clear visual hierarchy
- Minimal text, maximum clarity
- One primary action per screen

#### 3. Provide structure and routine
- Consistent weekly format (same process every Sunday)
- Predictable meal rotation
- Built-in flexibility (leftover/order-out nights)

#### 4. Satisfy completion drive
- Checkboxes everywhere for dopamine hits
- Status indicators showing progress
- Clear endpoints

#### 5. Eliminate anxiety triggers
- Show costs upfront (no surprises at checkout)
- Include time estimates (manage expectations)
- Give permission to deviate (Sunday order-out night is planned)

